==English==

===Etymology===
From the [[Hebrew]] חַנָּה (''Channah'' or ''Hannah''), meaning ''favour'', ''grace'', or ''[[grace]]d with [[child]]''.

===Proper noun===
'''Hannah'''
#{{given name|female|from Hebrew|}} A female [[given name]]

